---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Welcome to ChapinLab</h1>
			<blockquote>
				<p>
					"See first, think later, then test. But always see first. Otherwise you will only see what you were expecting."
				</p>
				<p>
					― Douglas Adams, <em><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/work/quotes/3078120" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">So Long, and Thanks for All the Fish</a></em>
				</p>
			</blockquote>
			<p>
				I'm <strong>Benjamin Chapin</strong>, a PhD candidate in Accounting at Virginia Commonwealth University. 
				My research explores how artificial intelligence, feedback systems, and emotions shape managerial 
				decision-making in accounting practice.
			</p>
			<h2>What You'll 'See' Here</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/research"><strong>Research</strong></a> — Working papers and publications on behavioral accounting, AI in accounting, and management control systems</li>
				<li><a href="/cv"><strong>CV</strong></a> — Academic background, teaching experience, and professional journey</li>
				<li><a href="/blog"><strong>Blog</strong></a> — Thoughts on accounting research, technology, outdoor adventures, and life as a doctoral student</li>
				<li><a href="/about"><strong>About</strong></a> — More about my background, interests, and what drives my work</li>
			</ul>
			<h2>Beyond Academia</h2>
			<p>
				When I'm not researching or teaching, you'll find me rock climbing, sailing, backpacking, or 
				tinkering with technology. I believe the best insights come from diverse experiences — whether 
				that's analyzing experimental data or finding the best route up a cliff face.
			</p>
			<p>
				Feel free to explore the site and <a href="/blog">check out recent posts</a> to see what I'm 
				currently thinking about.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
